Package: learnRdashboard
Title: Hockey R Learning Hub Shiny App
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Shelby", "Level", email = "shelby@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A modular Shiny dashboard pairing a curated R-for-sport-analytics
    learning roadmap with pre-loaded ice hockey datasets from the 'ISAR'
    package, so exercises can be practiced on real hockey data as you work
    through each phase. Built as an app-package following the 'leprechaun'
    scaffold: modules live in R/mod_*.R, the roadmap and dataset catalogue
    ship as real package data in data/ (built from data-raw/), and the app
    is launched with learnRdashboard::run().
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
Imports:
    bsicons,
    bslib,
    dplyr,
    DT,
    ggplot2,
    shiny
Suggests:
    ISAR,
    usethis
LazyData: true
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
